In this article, President Joe Biden recognizes National Veterans and Military Families Month and emphasizes the importance of supporting military and veteran families. He shares a personal experience of having his son deployed to Iraq and highlights the sacrifices made by millions of Americans in similar situations. President Biden discusses his administration's efforts to fulfill the obligation of caring for veterans and their families, including signing an executive order to support the economic security of military and veteran spouses, caregivers, and survivors. He also mentions signing bipartisan bills to expand services and benefits for veterans and their families, addressing issues such as toxic exposure, suicide prevention, and military justice reforms. The article concludes with President Biden proclaiming November 2023 as National Veterans and Military Families Month and calling upon the American people to honor veterans and military families.